        "content": "<p><strong>From:</strong> Andrea Vezzosi &lt;<a href=\"mailto:vezzosi.ndr@gmail.com\">vezzosi.ndr@gmail.com</a>&gt;</p>\n<p>Dear Mailing list,</p>\n<p>the thm_deps command shows the lemmas used to prove a theorem, how hard<br>\nwould it be to implement a version that also prints out the<br>\ninstantiation of free variables, at least for a specified subset of theorems?</p>\n<p>An example below to clarify:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Isabelle\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">right_id</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"x + 0 = x\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"1 + 0 = 1\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">rule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">right_id</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">done</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Here's what I get from <code>thm_deps test</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Isabelle\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">dependencies</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">3</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">protectD</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">protectI</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">right_id</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>what I would wish for:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Isabelle\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">thm_deps</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">with_instantiations</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">right_id</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">test</span>\n<span class=\"c\">(*</span>\n<span class=\"c\">dependencies: 3</span>\n<span class=\"c\">    protectD</span>\n<span class=\"c\">    protectI</span>\n<span class=\"c\">    right_id (x=1)</span>\n<span class=\"c\">*)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>or actually just an equivalent Isabelle/ML function of a type like <br>\n<code>thm list -&gt; thm -&gt; (thm * term list) list</code>.</p>\n<p>Best regards,<br>\nAndrea</p>",
